        {
            "endOffset": 169354,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Analogous asymptotic expansions of the bound state with respect to a small parameter appear in various spectral problems.",
            "startOffset": 169233,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 170404,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0280": {
                    "endOffset": 170342,
                    "startOffset": 170338
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "We also use some simple results of perturbation theory of linear operators, where the standard reference is [28], however we require some extensions of the classical results.",
            "startOffset": 170230,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 199409,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0110",
            "sentence": "Precisely, we derive a lower and an upper bound for the lowest eigenvalue in the weak coupling constant regime.",
            "startOffset": 199298,
            "title": "Remarks on non-compactly supported finite measures"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 198467,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0080",
                    "title": "Weakly coupled bound state"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0100",
            "sentence": "As a special case one gets the following statement.",
            "startOffset": 198416,
            "title": "Asymptotics of the eigenfunction corresponding to the weakly coupled bound state"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 199599,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0110",
            "sentence": "Furthermore, we show that the results obtained here allow to recover an information on the weak coupling constant asymptotics in cases for which previously known results are not applicable.",
            "startOffset": 199410,
            "title": "Remarks on non-compactly supported finite measures"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 170503,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Extensions of our results to non-compactly supported finite Kato class measures are also discussed.",
            "startOffset": 170404,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 172431,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "In Section 2.2 we prove some statements on non-analytic perturbation theory, which are hard to find in the literature.",
            "startOffset": 172313,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 169731,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0100": {
                    "endOffset": 169730,
                    "startOffset": 169717
                },
                "br0290": {
                    "endOffset": 169730,
                    "startOffset": 169717
                },
                "br0360": {
                    "endOffset": 169730,
                    "startOffset": 169717
                },
                "br0410": {
                    "endOffset": 169730,
                    "startOffset": 169717
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "For the similar problems in the one-dimensional case see [10,29,36,41].",
            "startOffset": 169660,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 170818,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0080": {
                    "endOffset": 170817,
                    "startOffset": 170811
                },
                "br0410": {
                    "endOffset": 170817,
                    "startOffset": 170811
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Using purely variational arguments combined with our main result for compactly supported measures we are able to obtain weak coupling asymptotics of the lowest eigenvalue for a class of non-compactly supported measures, which is in some respects wider also for regular potentials than the one considered in [8,41].",
            "startOffset": 170504,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 202605,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0110",
            "sentence": "For instance, we do not need the second condition in (1.1) for regular potentials.",
            "startOffset": 202523,
            "title": "Remarks on non-compactly supported finite measures"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 170229,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0060": {
                    "endOffset": 170202,
                    "startOffset": 170196
                },
                "br0110": {
                    "endOffset": 170191,
                    "startOffset": 170187
                },
                "br0120": {
                    "endOffset": 170176,
                    "startOffset": 170172
                },
                "br0390": {
                    "endOffset": 170202,
                    "startOffset": 170196
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Precisely saying, we use its generalization for potentials-measures from the generalized Kato class, which is rigorously established in [12], see also [11] and [5,39] for further modifications.",
            "startOffset": 170036,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 172543,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "In Sections 2.3 and 2.4 we complement known results on the operators related to the Birman\u2013Schwinger principle.",
            "startOffset": 172432,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 188630,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0030",
                    "title": "Preliminaries"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0070",
            "sentence": "Combining the statements of Remark 2.12 and (2.24) we get the claim.",
            "startOffset": 188562,
            "title": "Properties of the R\u03bcdx(\u22c5)-function"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 172312,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0110": {
                    "endOffset": 172246,
                    "startOffset": 172239
                },
                "br0120": {
                    "endOffset": 172246,
                    "startOffset": 172239
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "In Section 2.1 we provide necessary facts from [11,12] on self-adjoint free Laplacians perturbed by Kato-class measures.",
            "startOffset": 172192,
            "title": "Preliminaries"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 169957,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Our list of references is by no means complete, however many of closely related works are mentioned.",
            "startOffset": 169857,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 190525,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0080",
                    "title": "Weakly coupled bound state"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0090",
            "sentence": "In this subsection we compute the asymptotics of weakly coupled bound state.",
            "startOffset": 190449,
            "title": "Asymptotics of weakly coupled bound state"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 188633,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0030",
                    "title": "Preliminaries"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0070",
            "sentence": "\u25a1",
            "startOffset": 188632,
            "title": "Properties of the R\u03bcdx(\u22c5)-function"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 202522,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0080": {
                    "endOffset": 202502,
                    "startOffset": 202496
                },
                "br0410": {
                    "endOffset": 202502,
                    "startOffset": 202496
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0110",
            "sentence": "Note that with the aid of Theorems 4.1 and 4.4 one can obtain information on the asymptotics of the lowest eigenvalue also in those cases, where the results of [8,41] are not applicable.",
            "startOffset": 202336,
            "title": "Remarks on non-compactly supported finite measures"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 169801,
            "parents": [],
            "refoffsets": {
                "br0160": {
                    "endOffset": 169800,
                    "startOffset": 169790
                },
                "br0170": {
                    "endOffset": 169800,
                    "startOffset": 169790
                },
                "br0350": {
                    "endOffset": 169800,
                    "startOffset": 169790
                }
            },
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The analogous results for quantum graphs were obtained in [16,17,35].",
            "startOffset": 169732,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 193720,
            "parents": [
                {
                    "id": "se0080",
                    "title": "Weakly coupled bound state"
                }
            ],
            "secId": "se0090",
